column2: This is the first data on Jesse Lake connected to Sawyer Lake by channel 1/4 mile long 60 degrees northeast.
Sunny- 52 degrees- very little boat traffic in the last week because it was too cold to ski and very few fisherman.
Bubbles on top of water coming up from the bottom.
Public perception also due to suspended zooplankton would like to identify.  Clear and calm- the temperature is 82 degrees.
Two weeks after ice-out- cloudy and windy.
Air temperature 82 degrees.  Wind calm and cloudy. many dragonflies in the air.  Some bluegills spawning- bass and crappie finished spawning.
Record low temperature last night.  Light power boat (wake) activity.
Water level very low.  Was difficult to enter lake through channel.
1 fishing boat- air temp 78 F- purple loosestrife- could not do tests for 6 feet.  Water temp 72 F.
1 fishing boat- air temp 82 F- people at public campsites.
Air temp 70 F- no one around but us- slight breeze- sunshine with no clouds.  Water temp 54 F.
No boat activity- one deer came down to drink- calm and sunny day- mid 60's temperature.
No boat activity- mallard and female duck on shore- windy and overcast- temperature is 75 degrees- muskrat on lake.
No boat activity- one camper unit- temperature 72 degrees- cloudy but calm- quiet on lake- saw adult eagle.
Two fishing boats- sunny and calm- 75 degrees- saw adult eagle.
No boat activity- gray skies. 9 ducks on lake.  Tamarack trees are yellow.  Beautiful scenery.
Sunny- windy- the temperature is 75 degrees- kayakers at rustic campsite- and it is very quiet.
Sunny- light wind- very quiet- and there are lots of weeds growing in the lake.
Sunny and breezy- very quiet- the temperature is 73 degrees- and no one but us is on the lake.
Overcast and the temperature is 66 degrees.  Canoeing over we saw six ducks and a blue heron on Sawyer Lake.
Sunny; 80 degrees; no one on the lake; very quiet.
DEEP HOLE - COULD NOT GET A 6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE
